YES! YES! YES! #YesKaTimeAaGaya.

Honestly, motherhood is a constant tug of war between YES and NO. All moms want to say YES to make their babies happy but unfortunately, it’s not always possible. Especially when it comes to the food they want vs what’s actually good for them.

Like my two boys and their love for instant noodles. They just can’t get enough and I have to be the goalkeeper who blocks those requests for noodles. But not anymore - check out @slurrpfarm millet noodles - made with foxtail and little millets, these are baked and NOT FRIED, and contain NO MAIDA, making them an incredibly healthy and wholesome snack options.

So now in our house, it’s just like @anushkasharma says, no bolne ka time ab ja chuka hai cuz Slurrp Farm aa chuka hai! Go check out their yummy products now!

@atozdadartt In Dadar, Mumbai was my one stop shop for all my fabric, upholstery, wallpaper selections. They had a wide range of designs at reasonable prices. They also stock a variety of brands including Sabyasachi, D'decor & international brands. 
Everything from my curtains, to sofas, pillows and wallpaper was selected in this one shop and it took me just one visit to do so saving me so much time.

I recently tried a Korean Hair Spa ( stem cell scalp treatment) and it was such a relaxing and refreshing experience! They really focus on scalp health, which makes so much sense because a healthy scalp is the foundation for healthy hair. They used different tools and treatments to detoxify and clean the scalp, and it left my hair feeling so light and fresh. Plus, the whole process was incredibly calming—I didn’t want it to end! Definitely something I’d recommend trying if you’re looking to pamper your hair and yourself.

#Rawbeautywithshrima #shrimarai #koreanhairspa #viralkoreanhairspa

🎉 Our Epic Family Reunion Tradition! 🧿🪬

🔹 Every two years, family from across India (and even abroad!) gathers at our ancestral home.
🔹 A dedicated family committee organizes the event, managing funds and planning every detail & invitation is sent out to everyone with a schedule of the full day.
🔹 The day begins with prayers at our family temple and Naga Bana uniting us all in gratitude and tradition.
🔹 Fun and games for all—Housie, Bingo, lucky draws & even a tug of war enjoyed by kids and elders alike.
🔹 Entertainment takes center stage with plays, dances, and family performances.
🔹 We honor our eldest family members and celebrate the young achievers who make us proud.
🔹 Post the delicious lunch, a cozy nap section is set up for everyone to recharge!
🔹 All-day feasting—breakfast, lunch, and dinner served with love and laughter.
🔹 The highlight? Our annual group photo, capturing generations of love and connection.

It’s more than just an event—it’s a celebration of family, culture, and togetherness. A tradition that strengthens our bonds and keeps us rooted.

I hope by sharing this wonderful tradition your family starts it too.
